Business Durability (20-Year Model)
The website isn't just a newsletter landing page — it's the foundation for a media business that compounds over decades. Every page we build serves the business model, not just the content.
Revenue Evolution (Built Into the Site Architecture)
Year 1-3: Newsletter + Sponsorships (free tier)

The site IS the product. Every article builds SEO authority that compounds.
Subscribe page optimized for conversion (Sabri Suby-style copy)
Sponsor slots designed into article template (tasteful, native-feeling)
The archive becomes a searchable library — long-tail SEO goldmine

Year 3-5: Paid tier + Tools

Site architecture already has /topics/ hub pages — these become gated "playbooks"
Free tool pages (e.g., /tools/cac-calculator, /tools/seo-checker) — lead magnets that attract backlinks and high-intent traffic. We add these pages to the sitemap now even if they come later.
Pricing page (/pricing) — already planned in the nav structure for when premium launches

Year 5-10: Community + Courses

/community/ section — case study submissions, local business directory
/courses/ — deep-dive training built from the best article series
Contributor pages become credibility engines for consulting/speaking

Year 10+: Platform

The content library is the moat. 500+ articles with compounding SEO.
AI search citations (structured content gets cited by ChatGPT, Perplexity, etc.)
Syndication and licensing of the methodology

