Content Moat Strategy
The site is designed for content that compounds, not content that expires:

Searchable content (80% of articles) — "How to reduce CAC for restaurants," "AI phone answering for local businesses." These rank in Google AND get cited by AI search engines. They drive traffic for years.
Shareable content (20%) — "A restaurant owner didn't notice his phone was being answered by AI. For four days." These go viral, build brand, attract links.
Original data — the CAC spread article (23x difference across 11 restaurants) is EXACTLY the kind of proprietary data competitors can't replicate. The site should surface these data pieces prominently.
Template/tool content — future pages like "Free Restaurant Marketing Checklist" drive high-intent leads forever.

